lass=title> Backstab Range?</span><hr size=1> So I was fooling around in Sullon Zek test last night trying to get a handle on this whole &quot;rogue&quot; thing, and though I learned a bunch, also had some frustrations.  Primarily, way too many of my attempted backstabs didn't land because the person/mob was running away from me and (I presume) too far away.  Especially on the big races, I feel like I had to be in their underwear with them to be close enough to backstab...<br>
<br>
Anyone have experience with this?  are there any tricks to staying in range or knowing when you are in range?<br>
<br>
